records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
GUILTY plea entered to the charge in count 1, Operate under the influence-8th offense.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of eight (8) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision.  The Court finds the defendant not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and eligible for the Substance Abuse Program after he has served the first eighteen (18) months of confinement.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety;
2) Pay a $3,200.00 fine plus costs, total of $4,817.00.  $150.00 cash bail from 15 CF 240 applied with $$4,667.00 balance remaining;
3) Intoxicated Driver Assessment and Driver Safety Plan;
4) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
5) provide DNA sample.  (DNA Surcharge is not imposed since defendants DNA is most likely on file)
The defendant has credit for 50 days.
Minutes.
